title: For Sale:  Walther Model 9, Type II, .25 ACP, Pre-WWII
postcontent: For sale is a Walther Model 9, Type II .25 ACP.  Pre-WWII German production.  The Type II was manufactured from 1924-1934 and, based on the serial number, this pistol was likely manufactured around 1928.  Most of the Walther records were destroyed during the war, so production information has been pieced back together by Walther collectors and aficionados.  This pistol is completely original with no modifications.  The 6-round magazine has the flat base plate stamped with the Walther logo (earlier versions were rounded).  The grips are black checkered hard rubber with the Walther logo along the bottom of each grip.  Due to the age of the pistol (approx. 87 years old), the grips are slightly warped and a little loose, but it doesn't affect the functionality of the gun.  This pistol is a nice little piece of history and will make a great addition to your collection.                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                    Price is $400.  Cash only.  Must show driver's license and sign Bill-of-Sale.  No shippping.  Pick-up will be in Martinsville, about 20 minutes North of Bloomington or 45 minutes south of Indy.  I'm not interested in trades, so please don't ask me to.  Email me if you're interested or have any questions.  Thanks

I am selling my H&K 7.62/.308 with leupold scope and several upgrades, all in excelent condition, for $3500. I have almost $5000 invested into this amazing firearm. Any serious buyers can text me at 520 - two five seven - five eight 16.  
 
Here is some background info on this epic rifle
 
The actions by the US Government banning the importation of many advanced semi-automatic rifles has prevented rifles like the HK91, HK93, and HK94 from being brought into the US. However, the US Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, and Firearms has certified the SR9 Sporting Rifle, SR9(T) and the PSG1 Marksman's Rifle as legal for importation and civilian ownership.
 
The SR9 continues the tradition of the HK91 but with several important modifications that make it the ideal sporter, target rifle, and heavy-duty hunter. Polygonal rifling is standard on the SR9, the same bore profile found on the PSG1 Marksman's Rifle.
 
Also standard is the new MSG90 buffer system, a significant improvement over the older system found on HK imitations. This makes the SR9 rifle one of the lowest recoil semi-automatics in the world. It is equipped with a specially designed thumbhole stock constructed of kevlar-reinforced fiberglass that is both durable and ergonomic.
 
A target version of the SR9, the SR9(T) adds a special MSG90 adjustable buttstock, PSG1 trigger group, and a PSG1 contoured handgrip to the standard SR9 rifle configuration.

The HK45 also has a O-ring on the polygonal barrel to provide a better barrel to frame lock up to improve accuracy, A polygonal barre arel an added benefit to resistance to wear. A polygonal barrel will normally outlast a conventional “lands-and-grooves” barrel by thousands of rounds. The Hk-45 incorprated dual buffer recoil systems one in the slide and one in the grip to minimalize recoil to a minimal.I've spent alot of money on upgrades, such as having the barrel and slide polised, Night Sights installed, L.E.O kit & match grade trigger. I've not seen another like it no where.. My loss is your gain, looking to get a new toy.. $750 is just the pistol, $850 i'll throw in the HellFighter UnderBoss Laser/Light & box of Lawman 230gr JHP. title: For Sale:   NightHawk Custom Shadow Hawk 9MM 9Rd (2 mags) NS       RMR Sight Cut *RMR SOLD SEPERATELY / Threaded BRL
postcontent: The Shadow Hawk Government was designed with the help of Steve "Yeti" Fisher, formerly of Magpul Dynamics. Pulling from his background in law enforcement, training and his passion for competition, allowed a truly special pistol to be formed. The Shadow Hawk Government is a unique blending of the pistolsmithing skills at Nighthawk Custom along with Mr. Fisher, and the electronic sight geniuses at Trijicon. (When paired with the optional Trijicon RMR sight). Attention to detail starts with the one-piece machined steel magwell/mainspring housing for quick and sure reloading of the Shadow Hawk. You will notice the chiseled look and feel of the black, flat faced trigger preferred by competition shooters. The gun is topped front and rear with Heinie Ledge Straight Eight Tritium night sights. Your hands will quickly notice the high undercut on the trigger guard along with 25 LPI checkering on the front strap. The high beaver tail will amaze you with the almost seamless fit and finish. The black and gray spiral-cut G10 grips add a subtle highlight to the black Nitrite finish and the stainless bushing contrasts nicely with the slide and frame. The aggressive cocking serrations are not just for looks but provide a sure purchase to rack the slide.
